    <item>
      <title>Miku Over Link</title>
      <author>Modzzila4324</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/667961</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/667961#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">a53b983e0958e3299f496500dfbd8056d84586b3</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 23:49:46 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69d8391be5383.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69d8172485317.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69d817250953b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69d81725b7266.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/69d81725dded6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a &lt;b&gt;janky &lt;/b&gt;cosmetic mod that replaces links hero outfit with Miku Links casual outfit is buggy looking cause UV mapping is annoying and i couldn't get it to look nice so i gave in. The hair physics are a little janky as the twin tails work with the hat physics they work most the time, but it's my first mod so go easy on me.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a guide to install this mod on cemu.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For those who know how to use cemu just put the Miku folder from the zip file into cemus&lt;br&gt;graphicPacks folder and it should work. note this mod was made on the EU version&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1.Open cemu and hover over the file button on the toolbar on the top left corner&lt;br&gt;then click open cemu folder&lt;br&gt;2.Once in the cemu folder open the graphicPacks folder &lt;br&gt;3.then drop the Miku folder from the mod in the the graphicPacks folder&lt;br&gt;4.reboot cemu and right wind waker hd and click "edit graphics pack"&lt;br&gt;then in the mods tab you should see the Miku mod just tick it and load the game&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;note this was made for the EU version I got no clue if it works with the US version but I see no reason why it wouldn't.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;I recommend this mod by &lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1701022" data-id="member_1701022"&gt;SariaOfTheKokiri&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/50002"&gt;Female Dialogue Patch: HD Edition!&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;The mod was made for the US version but I got this to work on the EU version of the game by renaming the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;permanent_2d_UsEnglish.pack&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;to&lt;strong&gt; &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;permanent_2d_EuEnglish.pack &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I also had to add my games region title id to the .rules you can get your games id by right clicking it in cemu and you'll see &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;copy title ID&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; my rules.txt looked like this&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;pre&gt;[Definition]&lt;br&gt;titleIds = 0005000010143500,0005000010143500,0005000010143500,0005000010143600&lt;br&gt;name = FemaleDialogue&lt;br&gt;path = "The Legend of Zelda: The Wind Waker HD/Mods/Female Dialogue"&lt;br&gt;description = Female Dialogue&lt;br&gt;version = 4&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;I also recommend this mod by &lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/2059904" data-id="member_2059904"&gt;pellapellasekai&lt;/a&gt; who made the &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/sounds/86433"&gt;Full Linka Voice Port&lt;/a&gt; mod &lt;br&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;Again a mod for the US version but will work for the EU version with a little work.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a class="Avatar Offline" data-id="member_2457284" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/2457284" data-user-tooltip="" aria-expanded="false"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div class="Poster SelectedElement"&gt;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/2457284" data-id="member_2457284"&gt;ShiriaruKita&lt;/a&gt; left a handy comment on the mod page. &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/posts/13357805#post_13357805"&gt;Full comment&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"I renamed the "US" folder in content/cafe to "EU" (because I'm using the Europe version) and that fixed it. I see the rules.txt has the EU Title ID so it shows up in Graphics Packs but without changing that folder nothing will change."&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class="TimeStamp OlderThan1Day"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/miku_wind_waker_hd_mod.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Link</category>
      <category>Skins</category>
    </item>
